## CI/CD Pipeline and Configuration Management

This document describes the GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline setup and how configuration secrets and environment variables are managed.

---

### Pipeline Overview

The project uses three GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`:

| Workflow File | Name | Trigger | Purpose |
|---------------|------|---------|---------|
| `buildAndDeployToDockerHub_DEVELOPMENT.yaml` | `BuildContainersDevelopment` | Push to `main` | Build dev containers |
| `buildAndDeployToDockerHub_PRODUCTION.yaml` | `BuildContainersProduction` | Push to `production` | Build prod containers |
| `deployToServer.yaml` | `DeployChampDSAdmin` | After build workflows complete | Deploy to remote VM |

**Flow:**
```
Push to main/production
        â†“
Build Workflow (dev or prod)
        â†“
    Build Docker containers (server-app, nginx-and-website)
        â†“
    Push to Docker Hub
        â†“
Deploy Workflow (triggered on build success)
        â†“
    SCP files to remote server via jump bastion
        â†“
    docker compose up on remote server
```

---

### GitHub Environments

The pipelines use GitHub Environments to scope secrets:
- **`development`** - Used when workflow is `BuildContainersDevelopment`
- **`production`** - Used when workflow is `BuildContainersProduction`

Environment is selected dynamically:
```yaml
environment: ${{ github.workflow == 'BuildContainersProduction' && 'production' || 'development' }}
```

---

### Required GitHub Secrets (per environment)

| Secret | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` | Docker Hub login username |
| `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` | Docker Hub access token |
| `NPM_TOKEN` or `CDS_NPM_TOKEN` | NPM registry auth token for private packages |
| `CDS_NPM_REGISTRY` | (Optional) Custom NPM registry URL |
| `FULL_CONFIG_JSON64` | Base64-encoded full app configuration JSON |
| `SSH_KEY_GITHUB_DEPLOY` | Private SSH key for deployment to remote server |

### Required GitHub Variables (repository-level)

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `CDS_PROJECT_NAME` | Project identifier (e.g., `champdsadmin`) |

